p: According to the results obtained in the tests, it was found that (-)-fenchone at concentrations of 1024 to 16 Î¼g/mL does not show antibacterial activity against any of the tested bacterial strains. A study conducted by Balogun et al[ 54] demonstrated that the essential oil of Moringa oleifera at a concentration of 25 mg/mL. With monoterpenes as the most abundant class of compounds, exhibited relatively weak antibacterial activity against Staphylococcus aureus, Escherichia coli and Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
